OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FPay rises at fastest pace  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffor over 20 years          
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Wages have grown at the fastest rate in
OL,6, more than 20 years, but are still      
OL,7, failing to keep up with rising prices. 
OL,9,FAverage pay, including and excluding   
OL,10,Fbonuses, rose by 6.4% between September
OL,11,Fand November compared with the same    
OL,12,Fperiod in 2021, official figures show. 
OL,14,FIt is the fastest growth since 2001,   
OL,15,Fbut when adjusted for rising prices,   
OL,16,Fwages fell in real terms by 2.6%.      
OL,18,FThe gap between public and private     
OL,19,Fsector pay also remained close to a    
OL,20,Frecord high.                           
